---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import PullQuote from '../components/composition/PullQuote.astro';
import DataRow from '../components/primitives/DataRow.astro';
import ExternalLink from '../components/primitives/ExternalLink.astro';
import { author } from '../data/author';

const languages = [
  { label: 'FR', value: 'native' },
  { label: 'PT', value: 'native' },
  { label: 'EN', value: 'fluent' },
  { label: 'ES', value: 'reads' },
];

const trajectory = [
  { year: '2014', place: 'Paris' },
  { year: '2020', place: 'Lausanne · EPFL' },
  { year: '2022', place: 'Amsterdam · MIT' },
  { year: '2025', place: 'Rio · MIT founding' },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="French-Brazilian researcher and builder. MIT Senseable Rio, founding member. Trained in robotics at EPFL; urban science at MIT Amsterdam; now research line on informal urban morphology in Rio."
  ogType="profile"
  register="tropical"
>
  <article class="about-page grid-tropical">
    <div class="col-1-8 about-head">
      <h1 class="about-title">
        Théo<br />
        <em>Alessandro</em><br />
        Hermann
      </h1>
      <p class="about-positioning">
        Researcher and builder. French-Brazilian, based in Rio. Founding member of the MIT Senseable
        City Lab — Rio branch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-2-6 about-body">
      <PullQuote citation="Thesis · internal">
        Cartesian rigor applied to tropical complexity.
      </PullQuote>

      <p>
        The work splits two ways. On one side, urban science: how the geometry of cities — formal
        and informal — produces climate, exposure, and risk at the pedestrian scale. The current
        research line at MIT Senseable Rio maps favela morphology with LiDAR and translates it into
        CFD airflow, solar exposure, and environmental signal.
      </p>
      <p>
        On the other side, robotics. Open-source benchmarks for vision-language-action models on top
        of HuggingFace lerobot. World-model work on the edge of where perception, action, and
        learning meet.
      </p>
      <p>
        The two halves talk to each other more than they look like they should. Both deal in
        geometry, measurement, and acting on the world. Both reward building the artifact before
        announcing the result.
      </p>

      <PullQuote citation="Working principle">
        Frontier methods, messy systems. The favela is not a problem to be solved — it is a system
        to be understood.
      </PullQuote>
    </div>

    <aside class="col-7-8 marginalia">
      <section class="marginalia-block">
        <h4 class="mono-caption marginalia-heading">LANGUAGES</h4>
        {languages.map((l) => <DataRow label={l.label} value={l.value} />)}
      </section>
      <section class="marginalia-block">
        <h4 class="mono-caption marginalia-heading">TRAJECTORY</h4>
        {trajectory.map((t) => <DataRow label={t.year} value={t.place} />)}
      </section>
      <section class="marginalia-block">
        <h4 class="mono-caption marginalia-heading">CV</h4>
        <DataRow label="PDF">
          <ExternalLink href="/resume.pdf">Download</ExternalLink>
        </DataRow>
      </section>
      <section class="marginalia-block">
        <h4 class="mono-caption marginalia-heading">CONTACT</h4>
        <DataRow label="MAIL">
          <a href={`mailto:${author.email}`}>{author.email}</a>
        </DataRow>
      </section>
    </aside>
  </article>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem) var(--space-section);
    row-gap: var(--s-8);
  }

  .about-head {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-4);
  }
  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-tropical);
    font-weight: 450;
    font-size: var(--text-display-lg);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 0;
    font-variation-settings:
      'opsz' 36,
      'SOFT' 60;
  }
  .about-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-variation-settings:
      'opsz' 36,
      'SOFT' 100,
      'WONK' 1;
  }
  .about-positioning {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 44ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Body — generous Tropical rhythm: line-height 1.7, paragraph spacing
     from --s-6, larger than Cartesian. */
  .about-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    margin-block: 0 var(--s-6);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .about-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Marginalia — sticky asymmetric aside at col-7-8 (Phase 4.7 D4). */
  .marginalia {
    position: sticky;
    top: var(--s-16);
    height: fit-content;
    align-self: start;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-8);
  }
  .marginalia-block {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-2);
  }
  .marginalia-heading {
    margin: 0 0 var(--s-2);
    color: var(--color-oxblood);
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  @media (max-width: 719px) {
    .marginalia {
      position: static;
      margin-top: var(--s-12);
    }
  }
</style>
